WEBVTT

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:10.000
The Time - Current page allows you to enter hours worked for the current pay period. 

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.000
It also allows you to save your timesheet, submit your timesheet, and preview your timesheet before submitting it. 

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:22.000
At the top of the page, you will see the timesheet for the pay period and its status.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:27.000
The Trash Can icon allows you to delete all hours entered for a row. 

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:32.000
The Magnifying Glass icon allows you to view details about the project.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:39.000
In the timesheet entry field, the PROJECT column lists the name of the project. 

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:45.000
If you are working on multiple projects, you can select the relevant project from the dropdown menu.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:48.000
The TASK column displays the labor task name. 

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:54.000
If you are assigned to different tasks, you can choose the appropriate task from the dropdown menu.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:02.000
The PAY CODE column shows the available pay codes, including RT (regular time) and OT (overtime). 

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:05.000
In the input fields for each day, enter the number of hours worked. 

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:11.000
Your manager will provide specific details on how to allocate hours across projects. 

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:14.000
Full-time employees must log a minimum of 8 hours per day.

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:20.000
For additional hours worked that exceed 8 hours a day, follow your organization's overtime policy. 

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:27.000
Part-time employees should adhere to the specific guidelines outlined by their organization's policy.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:33.000
If you're working on multiple projects, select the appropriate project from the dropdown menu. 

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:37.000
The task and pay code will be filled in automatically. 

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:41.000
Afterward, you can enter the hours worked for each project.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:47.000
If you need additional rows to enter more projects, click the Add Row icon at the bottom of the timesheet.

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:54.000
The Comments section allows you to enter any notes or comments for your manager regarding the active timesheet. 

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:56.000
Adding comments is optional.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:59.000
Click the Save button to save your timesheet. 

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
It is important to save your work frequently to avoid losing entered data.

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:07.000
To submit your timesheet for approval, click the Submit button. 

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
Ensure that you follow your organization's guidelines for when to submit your timesheet.

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:17.000
The Preview button lets you preview your active timesheet. 

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:23.000
Finally, the My Projects button provides a list of all your active projects. 

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:29.000
For more information about managing your projects, refer to the Time - My Projects Page video module.